'''هېنري جورج راورټي''' (31 د مۍ، 1825 – 20 د اکتوبر 1906) (په انګرېزي:Henry George Raverty) د برتانيوي هند يو پوځی افسر او ژبپوه وه.

==ژوند==

He served from 1843 to 1864, rising to the rank of Major in the 3rd Bombay Native Infantry.<ref>{{ODNBweb|id=35686|title=Raverty, Henry George (1825–1906)|first=Schuyler|last=Jones}}</ref>

Raverty fought in the Punjab campaign of 1849–1850 and [[Swat (Pakistan)|Swat]] campaign of 1850. He compiled a [[gazetteer]] of [[Peshawar]]. While serving in Peshawar he was taught [[Pashto]] by the scholar Abdur Rahman Khan Muhammadzai<ref>[http://www.dawn.com/weekly/books/archive/030316/books4.htm Articles: Thinking like a Pathan – Dawn Pakistan]</ref> and he began to study [[Afghan poetry]].<ref>[http://www.the-south-asian.com/April2004/Books-Pathans-2.htm ''The Pathans – Classic Works & Reading'']</ref> 

On retirement from the army, he returned to England and continued his oriental studies, culminating in his vast ''Notes on Afghanistan and part of Baluchistan'' and his unpublished ''History of Herat''. He died in [[Cornwall]], England in 1906.

